milestone.title: Sprint 1
milestone.description:
General instructions
At least one blank line must be left between each question.
In the simple form, the question comes first, then the answers are set in between brackets, with an equal sign (=) indicating the correct answer(s) and tilde (~) the wrong answers. A hash (#) will insert a response. Questions can be weighted by placing percentage signs (%..%) around the weight. Comments are preceded by double slashes (//) and are not imported.

513743220.title: Refactor tests
513743220.body:
All the tests now use a function I made called getTestCases which is passed an array of correct answers and an array of incorrect answers. It builds full questions (adding title, question text, and braces) and adds some basic checks (creating questions with invalid characters, creating questions that are missing different parts), then it returns an array of all of these questions which are used in the tests. So each individual test just supplies answers. It removes a lot of duplicate code.

Additionally, if we ever want to add new checks, or change which characters are valid, where newlines are valid, etc, it can all be done inside this function.

True False: Anything else

507924317.title: Issue30
507924317.body:
Created a demo for sprint one
This includes:
A QuestionType enum
A displayQuestions method in GiftVerifier which takes in a file and echos all the questions in it along with their types or INVALID
A getQuestionTypes method in GiftVerifier which takes a question and returns the enum corresponding to its type
An extractQuestions method in GiftVerifier which takes a string of input and splits it into an array of questions. I foresee a lot more being added to this method to check for valid question formats, stripping lines, etc
A testQuestions.txt file which has some of each type of question, each looking a bit different and a few incorrectly formatted questions
A SprintOneDemo class which contains a main method which takes a filename and runs the displayQuestions function on it.
sprintOneDemo in the makefile which compiles everything and runs SprintOneDemo with testQuestions.txt as the argument

Additionally:
Some corrections were made to the regex constants and those in the matches
These corrections added \r in addition to \n in the places where newlines could be. Inside of questions, \n* was changed to \n? since there may only be one newline at a time inside of a question (no consecutive newlines).

These new methods determine whether a string representing the answers of a question is intended to be a particular type of question.

Matching: Contains =omitChars*->
Multiple Answer: isn't matching, contains ~\s*%
Single Answer isn't matching or multiple answer, contains ~ or =
True False: Anything else

milestone.title: Sprint 1
milestone.description:
General instructions
At least one blank line must be left between each question.
In the simple form, the question comes first, then the answers are set in between brackets, with an equal sign (=) indicating the correct answer(s) and tilde (~) the wrong answers. A hash (#) will insert a response. Questions can be weighted by placing percentage signs (%..%) around the weight. Comments are preceded by double slashes (//) and are not imported.

507924317.title: Issue30
507924317.body:
Created a demo for sprint one
This includes:
A QuestionType enum
A displayQuestions method in GiftVerifier which takes in a file and echos all the questions in it along with their types or INVALID
A getQuestionTypes method in GiftVerifier which takes a question and returns the enum corresponding to its type
An extractQuestions method in GiftVerifier which takes a string of input and splits it into an array of questions. I foresee a lot more being added to this method to check for valid question formats, stripping lines, etc
A testQuestions.txt file which has some of each type of question, each looking a bit different and a few incorrectly formatted questions
A SprintOneDemo class which contains a main method which takes a filename and runs the displayQuestions function on it.
sprintOneDemo in the makefile which compiles everything and runs SprintOneDemo with testQuestions.txt as the argument

Additionally:
Some corrections were made to the regex constants and those in the matches
These corrections added \r in addition to \n in the places where newlines could be. Inside of questions, \n* was changed to \n? since there may only be one newline at a time inside of a question (no consecutive newlines).
